Subject: Thank Your Legislator for Improving Public Health with Smokefree

Comment: Dear Governor Beverly Perdue: In honor of the Great American Smokeout, I'd like to thank you for making restaurants and bars in North Carolina smoke free. The Great American Smokeout is a day to encourage smokers to stop smoking for good. By passing a smoke-free law, North Carolina's government has made it that much easier for smokers to give up the deadly habit. Our smoke-free law will help protect smokers and non-smokers alike from the dangers of tobacco smoke. Smoking causes nearly 12,000 deaths per year in North Carolina, and an additional 1,000 non-smokers die because of exposure to secondhand smoke. Smoking costs North Carolina taxpayers $2.46 billion in direct healthcare costs, including $769 million in Medicaid expenses alone. Going smoke free will help change all that. Starting January 2, we'll be on the road to diminished health costs and lower death and disease rates. That's a lasting legacy to be proud of. Thank you for your efforts to improve public health in North Carolina, and please continue to support lifesaving policies. Sincerely, James Dillehay 2814 Redwood Rd Durham, NC 27704-4030

